snippet.textDisplay:
Shen Yun Performing Arts presented inspiring stories from the past and present to theatergoers in Australia, Canada, France, and the United States, during the second week of March 2020.


Shen Yun presented the 14th performance of its Sydney tour at the Capitol Theatre in Australia on March 14, 2020.


New York-based Shen Yun Performing Arts at Le Corum in Montpellier, France, on March 13, 2020.


Curtain call by Shen Yun performers at the Southern Alberta Jubilee Auditorium in Calgary, Alberta, Canada, on March 9, 2020.


Shen Yun Performing Arts at the David H. Koch Theater at Lincoln Center on March 8, 2020.

“Magical and Extraordinary”

Classical pianist Emmanuel Ferrer-Laloë

Emmanuel Ferrer-Laloë, an award-winning classical pianist, saw Shen Yun at Le Corum in Montpellier, France, on March 12, 2020.

“[The orchestra] was excellent... This is very well done,” he said.

“The expression of the dancers, in their movements really expresses a lot of things, feelings, and impressions. It’s very, very, very well done!

“There is a palpable message behind it, a spiritual message. This traditional aspect is also very important. Traditions must be preserved.

“Today, there is a welcomed reaction to the ambient materialism... I believe that the aspiration of art is precisely to convey messages, to convey peace, a transcendental vision of humanity and what it constitutes.

“If they practice this meditation, if they practice this way of doing things, obviously, it is the best way to generate beneficial energy, so, they can give the maximum!

“It’s wonderful! It’s magical and extraordinary with a lot of precision and a lot of finesse,” Mr. Ferrer-Laloë concluded.
